Thomas Tuchel’s discussion with midfielders, N’Golo Kante, Jorginho and Mateo Kovacic has been revealed. According to ESPN, the German, on his arrival at Stamford Bridge in January, told the three midfielders that he would be relying on them to lead by example at the base of the club’s midfield The German tactician also told them that he would rotate them depending on the game plan. Furthermore, he let the midfield stars understand that their fitness level and the opposition will matter, according to reports. There have been obvious changes since the former Borussia Dortmund manager took charge at Chelsea earlier this year. Reports suggest that former manager, Frank Lampard and some of the top players at the club had some issues with Lampard clearly losing the dressing room.